  "prompt": "Why does Dream11(dot)com is not Illegal in India?",
  "response": "Dream11 is considered legal in India primarily because it is classified as a game of skill rather than a game of chance. Here are the key reasons:\n\n1. Supreme Court Recognition\n- The Supreme Court of India has ruled that fantasy sports platforms like Dream11 involve substantial skill and are not gambling\n- Skill is determined by the participant's knowledge, understanding, and analysis of players' performance and game dynamics\n\n2. Legal Framework\n- Games of skill are exempt from gambling laws in India\n- Players must use their knowledge of sports, player statistics, and performance to create teams\n- Success depends more on participants' expertise than random chance\n\n3. Selection Process\n- Players must strategically select players based on:\n- Previous performance\n- Current form\n- Player statistics\n- Team composition\n- Player fitness\n- Match conditions\n\n4. Regulatory Compliance\n- Dream11 follows strict guidelines and regulations\n- Transparent platform with clear rules\n- Age restrictions (18+ only)\n- Responsible gaming practices\n\n5. Court Judgments\n- Multiple court verdicts, including the Gujarat High Court and Supreme Court, have supported fantasy sports platforms\n- Considered a legitimate form of online gaming\n\nThese factors contribute to Dream11's legal status in India, distinguishing it from gambling platforms.",
